<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<span id="head-c1bb273a69a87597ff4a70e8c857e0c40495a91a"><h3 id="l1">Page Editing</h3></span>
<p id="l2">
Editing a page is as simple as clicking on the "Edit" icon at the top of the screen or the edit link in the page footer. 
</p>
<p id="l4">
There are many possible options for markup. For your convenience, there is a formatting toolbar, which works very much like a toolbar in a word processor. By highlighting text and clicking one of the buttons, such as Bold, the text will be surrounded by the appropriate markup to make it appear bold. 
</p>
<p id="l6">
Always make sure you "Preview" before you "Save Changes", otherwise you might end up editing a page several times. 
</p>
<p id="l8">
The following pages describe the elements (wiki markup) you can use to get special formatting effects: <br/>
</p>

        <ul>

        <li>
<p id="l9">
 <a title="Help/Help on Formatting" href="Help_on_Formatting">Help on Formatting</a> - general text formatting rules <br/>
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p id="l10">
 <a title="Help/Help on Linking" href="Help_on_Linking">Help on Linking</a> - external hyperlinks and inline images <br/>
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p id="l11">
 <a title="Help/Help on Headlines" href="Help_on_Headlines">Help on Headlines</a> - section headings <br/>
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p id="l12">
 <a title="Help/Help on Lists" href="Help_on_Lists">Help on Lists</a> - lists and indented sections <br/>
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p id="l13">
 <a title="Help/Help on Tables" href="Help_on_Tables">Help on Tables</a> - tables <br/>
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p id="l14">
 <a title="Help/Help with Images" href="Help_with_Images">Help with Images</a> - images <br/>
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p id="l15">
 <a title="Help/Help with Macros" href="Help_with_Macros">Help with Macros</a> - macros are magic things <tt>[[LikeThis]]</tt> 
</p>
</li>

        </ul>


<p id="l17">
To experiment with wiki markup, go to the <a title="Sandbox" href="../Sandbox">Sandbox</a> and then click on the Edit tab on the top of the page. Use your browser's "open a new window with this link" feature on the word "Wiki Sand Box", so you can keep the help pages open side-by-side to the editing window. 
</p>
<p id="l20">
For a list of other Help topics, see the <a title="Help" href="../Help">Help Documentation</a>. 
</p>
